	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories  Police are looking for a 15-year-old girl who reportedly
went missing in Hout Bay yesterday, Tuesday 7 August. Warrant Officer Tanya Lesch says Leah Hall  was allegedly last seen at a shop in Victoria
Road wearing grey pants, takkies with green and gold stripes and a pink beanie
between 15:00 and 17:00. It is reported that her cell phone is on voicemail. Circumstances around her disappearance are still unknown and
an investigation is underway. Anyone with information is urged to call the investigating
officer, Captain Jacques Lourens, on 082 469 2921.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  